16/05/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Starting Tuesday (17 May), Ohrid hosts a two-day meeting of the defence ministers and army chiefs of Albania, Bulgaria and Macedonia. 
Talks will focus on regional military co-operation and the bids of Albania and Macedonia to join NATO. 
Bulgaria is already a member.
In other news, the third annual conference of the central banks in the Balkans begins Monday in the Bulgarian resort of St Konstantin and Elena. 
Participants will discuss economic planning and forecasting. 
(Makfax - 16/05/05; Bulgarian National Bank Web site - 13/05/05)
